   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For DSF&apos;s sustainable aquaculture program, which aims to ensure that production practices in Canada&apos;s fish farming industry carry as few negative environmental and biological impacts on wild fish populations and marine ecosystems as is possible. DSF is working to evaluate and improve interim protection for migrating juvenile salmon in the Broughton Archipelago, and to establish the economic viability of a closed containment farm system. The organization will continue to advocate for science-based sustainability standards for major Canadian retailers and sound assessments of the environmental impacts of production practices. DSF&apos;s program includes efforts to improve marketing, labeling, and purchasing practices in Canada&apos;s seafood market</narrative>
